{
  "texts": [
    "To speed up the training and inferring process, we use the simple average pooling representation of randomly extracted 8 frames from a video as the soft video tokens, which often leads to visual information loss.",
    "It may achieve lower performance compared to strong video-LLMs such as Video-ChatGPT which focuses more on fine-grained visual representations of a video and its temporal encoding.",
    "We also fed LLMs with the audio tokens obtained by the audio or speech encoders and connectors.",
    "Experimental results indicate that Uni-MoE trained with MoE-Task3 achieves the best performance on Activity-QA among strong video baselines, surpassing Video-ChatGPT by 7.5%.",
    "Moreover, it also achieves comparative performance on the MSVD-QA dataset."
  ]
}